<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active from early spring till mid-autumn and range in total length 11-15 mm and 4-6 mm in maximum width. The species is mainly nocturnal and promptly attracted to artificial lights. In Hong Kong, larvae of this species bore into wood of 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Sulidae" genus="Morus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Morus alba" order="Ciconiiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Morus alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Elsewhere, larval host plants include also 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Albizia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Albizia julibrissin" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="julibrissin">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Albizia julibrissin</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ulmaceae" genus="Celtis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Celtis sinensis" order="Urticales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Celtis sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ficus pumila" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ficus pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lauraceae" genus="Machilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Machilus thunbergii" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="thunbergii">
